Nyrix Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 1 June 2026

Nyrix is a Discord bot created by Nyro. This Privacy Policy explains what information Nyrix collects, why it is used, and how users or server owners can request data removal.

By adding Nyrix to a Discord server or using Nyrix commands, you agree to this Privacy Policy.

1. Information Nyrix Collects

Nyrix may collect and store limited Discord data needed for the bot to work properly.

This may include:

Discord server IDs
Discord server names
Discord user IDs
Discord usernames or mentions
Discord channel IDs
Discord role IDs
Bot setup settings
Admin user IDs added by the server owner
Moderation log settings
Welcome, goodbye, ticket, review, suggestion, verification, rank, XP and leaderboard settings
Casino balances
Casino cooldowns
Level, rank and prestige data
Warning, mute, kick, ban and unban action details
Ticket information created through the bot
Suggestion and review content submitted through the bot
Message content only when needed for bot features, commands, moderation, locked channels, chatbot replies, secret commands, XP, reviews, suggestions, or ticket features

Nyrix does not collect passwords, payment card details, private Discord login details, or any information outside Discord.

2. Why Nyrix Uses This Data

Nyrix uses stored data to provide its features, including:

Moderation commands such as kick, ban, mute, warn, clear and unban
Server logging
Admin promotion and demotion
Tickets
Verification
Welcome and goodbye messages
Reviews and suggestions
Casino games and casino balances
Daily and crime cooldowns
Levels, XP, prestige, ranks and leaderboards
Bot safety, abuse prevention and banned server checks
Bot support and troubleshooting

Nyrix only uses Discord data to run bot features. Nyrix does not sell user data. Nyrix does not use user data for advertising. Nyrix does not share user data with data brokers.

3. Message Content

Nyrix may read message content in servers where it is installed because some features need it to work.

Message content may be used for:

Detecting chatbot trigger phrases
Detecting secret casino commands
Deleting messages from locked review, suggestion or leaderboard channels
Giving XP for normal chat activity
Moderation and logging features where enabled
Ticket, review and suggestion systems

Nyrix does not read messages from servers it is not in. Nyrix does not access private Discord messages unless the bot sends or receives a DM as part of a bot feature.

4. Data Storage

Nyrix stores data in local JSON files used by the bot. These files may include server settings, user IDs, balances, cooldowns, ranks, prestige, XP and banned server records.

Data is kept only for as long as needed to provide the bot’s features, keep server settings working, prevent abuse, or support moderation records.

5. Data Sharing

Nyrix does not sell, rent or trade user data.

Data may only be seen by:

The bot developer, for support, maintenance and safety
Server owners or admins, through bot logs and bot commands
Discord, as part of Discord’s own platform and API services
Hosting providers used to run the bot

6. Server Owner Controls

Server owners can control many Nyrix features by using the bot setup commands.

Server owners can remove or change:

Log channels
Review channels
Suggestion channels
Ticket settings
Verification settings
Welcome and goodbye settings
Leaderboard settings
XP and rank settings
Admin access added through Nyrix

Removing Nyrix from a server stops the bot from collecting new data from that server.

7. Data Removal

A user or server owner can request removal of stored Nyrix data by contacting Nyro.

Contact:
Discord Username: its_nyro
Support Server: https://discord.gg/TqQtTxmsHF

When requesting data removal, include:

